# Multi-agent workflow (MerchantHub AI)

Use this when building features via the PM / Architect / Tester cycle.

## Sequence (mandatory)

```
PM (slice brief) → Architect (tech spec) → Builder (code) → Tester (report) → PM (accept)
```

Do not skip steps. Do not implement before Architect fills the technical section.

## Artifact locations

| Stage | Output | Path |
|-------|--------|------|
| PM | Slice brief | `docs/agents/slices/S-XXX-*.md` |
| Architect | Tech spec + optional ADR | Same slice file + `docs/agents/adrs/` |
| Builder | Code + doc updates | `backend/`, `frontend/`, `docs/API_REFERENCE.md` |
| Tester | Test plan + report | `docs/agents/test-plans/`, `docs/agents/test-reports/` |
| PM | Accept / rework | Update slice `Status` field |

## Slice sizing

- One slice = one PR-sized vertical feature
- Align to phases in `docs/MERCHANTHUB_AI_BUILD_PROMPT.md` (Foundation → Core → AI → Dashboards → Polish)
- Examples: "customer review submit", "merchant AI insights", "admin approve business"

## Read order per agent

1. `docs/MERCHANTHUB_AI_BUILD_PROMPT.md` (product context)
2. Current slice file in `docs/agents/slices/`
3. Linked ADR if present
4. Relevant docs: `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `ERD.md`, `API_REFERENCE.md`

## Conflict resolution

| Dispute | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| User value / UX / AC wording | Product Manager |
| API shape, schema, layering, NFRs | Architect |
| Test coverage / release readiness | Tester |
| AI phrasing must be "suggestion" | Product Manager |
| Implementation style | Existing builder rules (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`) |

## Parallel work

- PM + Architect may draft **next** slice while Builder implements **current**
- Tester writes test plan as soon as Architect API contract is done (TDD-friendly)
- Tester runs verification after Builder completes

## Definition of done (full cycle)

- [ ] All acceptance criteria numbered and testable
- [ ] Architect checklist complete on slice file
- [ ] Code merged with builder rules satisfied
- [ ] Every AC mapped to a test in test report
- [ ] PM set `Status: Accepted` on slice file

## Invoking roles

Tell the agent explicitly: *"Act as Product Manager for slice S-00X"* or *"Run full cycle for S-00X"*.

Builder work uses existing rules: `backend-fastapi`, `frontend-nextjs`, `ai-and-integrations`, etc.
